    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.2: Authors show that furosemide can be used to distinguish alpha1 from alpha6 containing GABAArs.\n\nFig.3+4: Application of furosemide prevents or reverses synaptic strengthening induced by mROS.\n\nNote: \"Synaptic strengthening' is the effect of having more (alpha6-containing) GABAARs in the postsynaptic specialization that together generate more current and a resulting larger influence on the membrane potential. The application of the furosemide silences the newly aquired population of GABAARs at the synapse, masking the synaptic strengthening.. Experimental description: \"Mice were anesthetized with isoflurane and immediately decapitated\"",
